.Dd July 10, 2026
.Dt NUMFMT 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm numfmt
.Nd convert numbers to or from human-readable form
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl z
.Op Fl d Ar char
.Op Fl f Ar field
.Op Fl -from Ns = Ns Ar unit
.Op Fl -to Ns = Ns Ar unit
.Op Fl -header Ns Op = Ns Ar lines
.Op Fl -invalid Ns = Ns Ar mode
.Op Fl -padding Ns = Ns Ar width
.Op Fl -round Ns = Ns Ar method
.Op Fl -suffix Ns = Ns Ar suffix
.Op Ar number ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility converts numbers between plain numeric and human-readable forms.
It provides a BSD-licensed subset of the GNU
.Nm
interface commonly used by scripts.
.Pp
If
.Ar number
operands are specified, each operand is converted and printed on its own line.
Otherwise,
.Nm
reads standard input and converts the selected field on each input line.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl d Ar char , Fl -delimiter Ns = Ns Ar char
Use
.Ar char
as the input field delimiter instead of blank-separated fields.
.It Fl f Ar field , Fl -field Ns = Ns Ar field
Convert the numbered input field.
The first field is field 1.
.It Fl -format Ns = Ns Ar format
Use
.Ar format
as a
.Xr printf 3
format string when no output scaling is requested.
.It Fl -from Ns = Ns Ar unit
Scale input numbers from
.Ar unit .
Supported values are
.Cm none ,
.Cm auto ,
.Cm si ,
.Cm iec ,
and
.Cm iec-i .
.It Fl -header Ns Op = Ns Ar lines
Copy the first
.Ar lines
input lines without conversion.
If
.Ar lines
is omitted, one header line is copied.
.It Fl -invalid Ns = Ns Ar mode
Control invalid-number handling.
Supported modes are
.Cm abort ,
.Cm fail ,
.Cm warn ,
and
.Cm ignore .
.It Fl -padding Ns = Ns Ar width
Pad converted output to
.Ar width
columns.
Positive values right-align and negative values left-align.
.It Fl -round Ns = Ns Ar method
Use the specified rounding method.
Supported methods are
.Cm nearest ,
.Cm up ,
.Cm down ,
.Cm from-zero ,
and
.Cm towards-zero .
.It Fl -suffix Ns = Ns Ar suffix
Strip
.Ar suffix
from input numbers and append it to scaled output numbers.
.It Fl -to Ns = Ns Ar unit
Scale output numbers to
.Ar unit .
Supported values are
.Cm none ,
.Cm si ,
.Cm iec ,
and
.Cm iec-i .
Scaled output is formatted with
.Xr humanize_number 3 .
.It Fl z , Fl -zero-terminated
Use NUL instead of newline as the input and output record separator.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Dl $ numfmt --to=si 1500
.Dl 1.5k
.Pp
.Dl $ numfmt --from=iec --to=si 1K
.Dl 1.1k
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr humanize_number 3
.Sh CAVEATS
The
.Nm
utility implements the GNU options listed above.
It is not a complete implementation of every GNU
.Nm
extension.
